Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.12,0:12:09.54,1080CN_UPPER,,0,0,0,,字幕翻译给虫 欢迎点赞投币收藏转发分享关注充电评论
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.58,0:00:02.92,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,开头8秒的防不胜防，就不翻译了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.58,0:00:02.92,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,This video was made possible by Squarespace.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.00,0:00:07.50,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,有兴趣看下面链接吧
Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.00,0:00:07.50,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Build your beautiful website for 10% off at squarespace.com/Wendover.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:08.04,0:00:13.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,想象一条铁路线，能9小时内从华盛顿特区到德州的达拉斯……
Dialogue: 2,0:00:08.04,0:00:13.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Imagine a train that took you from Washington, DC to Dallas, Texas in nine hours…
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.68,0:00:17.10,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,或者9小时内从法国巴黎到雅典……
Dialogue: 2,0:00:13.68,0:00:17.10,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,or Paris, France to Athens, Greece in nine hours…
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.20,0:00:21.42,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,或者9小时内从南澳洲的阿德莱德到西澳洲的珀斯
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.20,0:00:21.42,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,or Adelaide, South Australia to Perth, Western Australia in nine hours.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:21.70,0:00:26.90,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而这些铁路线实际需要44小时、44小时、41小时
Dialogue: 2,0:00:21.70,0:00:26.90,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,These train trips actually take 44 hours, 44 hours, and 41 hours respectively
Dialogue: 1,0:00:26.90,0:00:32.14,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,所以让火车在9小时内完成这些旅途简直天方夜谭
Dialogue: 2,0:00:26.90,0:00:32.14,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,so the idea of making any of these trips by train in nine hours seems almost absurd.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:32.34,0:00:34.50,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但在中国，这却是家常便饭
Dialogue: 2,0:00:32.34,0:00:34.50,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,In China, though, that’s reality.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:34.51,0:00:39.00,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,2018年9月，中国开通了一条新的高铁线路
Dialogue: 2,0:00:34.51,0:00:39.00,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,In September 2018, the country opened up a brand new high speed rail route
Dialogue: 1,0:00:39.00,0:00:41.68,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,从香港直达北京
Dialogue: 2,0:00:39.00,0:00:41.68,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,with direct trains from Hong Kong to Beijing.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.03,0:00:47.02,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,距离和达拉斯到华盛顿特区、巴黎到雅典、阿德莱德到珀斯差不多
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.03,0:00:47.02,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,This is about the same distance as DC to Dallas, Paris to Athens, or Adelaide to Perth
Dialogue: 1,0:00:47.18,0:00:51.46,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而该线路全程只需8小时56分钟
Dialogue: 2,0:00:47.18,0:00:51.46,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,and yet these trains make the trip in only 8 hours and 56 minutes.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:51.64,0:00:56.94,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,更牛逼的是，十年前的2008年，北京还在开奥运会的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:00:51.64,0:00:56.94,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,What makes this even more impressive is that ten years ago, in 2008, at the time of the Beijing Olympics
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.04,0:01:00.24,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国高铁线路这有这些
Dialogue: 2,0:00:57.04,0:01:00.24,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,China’s high-speed rail network consisted of this.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:00.32,0:01:04.70,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,我们甚至得放大才能看清，一条是30公里的磁悬浮线路
Dialogue: 2,0:01:00.32,0:01:04.70,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,We’ll have to zoom in because the extent of the network was one 19 mile-long Maglev train
Dialogue: 1,0:01:04.70,0:01:07.00,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,从上海浦东国际机场到上海城区边缘
Dialogue: 2,0:01:04.70,0:01:07.00,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,from Shanghai Airport to the outskirts of Shanghai
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.00,0:01:11.04,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,和一条北京到天津的高铁线路
Dialogue: 2,0:01:07.00,0:01:11.04,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,and a traditional high-speed rail line from Beijing to the coastal city of Tianjin.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:11.26,0:01:15.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,十年后的今天，中国高铁网络变成了这样
Dialogue: 2,0:01:11.26,0:01:15.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Today, ten years later, that network has expanded into this.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:15.70,0:01:20.34,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国高铁线路全长是发过的8倍，日本的10倍
Dialogue: 2,0:01:15.70,0:01:20.34,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,China has 8 times as much high speed track as France, 10 times as much as Japan,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:20.46,0:01:25.06,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,英国的20倍，美国的500倍
Dialogue: 2,0:01:20.46,0:01:25.06,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,20 times as much as the UK, and 500 times as much as the US.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.16,0:01:30.58,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,实际上，中国的高铁线路长度比其他国家的加一起还要长
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.16,0:01:30.58,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,In fact, China has as much high-speed rail track as the rest of the world combined.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:30.74,0:01:35.56,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国竟然能在短短十年内取得如此伟大的成就
Dialogue: 2,0:01:30.74,0:01:35.56,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,It is staggering the amount of progress they have made in such a short amount of time.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:35.90,0:01:42.28,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,传统的高铁只存在于小的富有的国家，比如德国法国日本
Dialogue: 2,0:01:35.90,0:01:42.28,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Traditionally high speed rail exists in small countries with rich populations by the likes of Germany, France, and Japan.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.42,0:01:44.24,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国既不小也不富有
Dialogue: 2,0:01:42.42,0:01:44.24,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,China is neither of these things.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:44.40,0:01:49.26,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国很大，和美国差不多，也一点不富有
Dialogue: 2,0:01:44.40,0:01:49.26,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The country is enormous, about the same size as the US, and is also not rich.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.44,0:01:53.74,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,虽然不算贫穷，但中国只是一个中等收入国家
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.44,0:01:53.74,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,While no longer poor, China is definitively a middle income country.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.88,0:01:56.84,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,和墨西哥、泰国、巴西差不多
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.88,0:01:56.84,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,It’s about as rich as Mexico, Thailand, or Brazil.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:57.08,0:02:00.78,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,事实上，尽管身为世界上拥有高铁里程最多的国家
Dialogue: 2,0:01:57.08,0:02:00.78,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,In fact, despite being the country with the most high speed rail in the world,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.94,0:02:04.84,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国却是拥有高铁的国家里最穷的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.94,0:02:04.84,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,China is also the poorest country in the world to have any high speed rail.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:04.98,0:02:11.03,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,虽然中国很大，但东部的人口密度却非常高
Dialogue: 2,0:02:04.98,0:02:11.03,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Despite the country’s vast size, China’s huge population makes it very dense especially in the east half.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.10,0:02:14.24,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,所以中国的确有很多大型城市群
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.10,0:02:14.24,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,This means that China does have large cities close enough together
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.24,0:02:17.02,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,就很适合乘火车在城市群内通勤
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.24,0:02:17.02,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,where it makes sense to take the train rather than the plane.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:17.16,0:02:24.18,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而比如广州到长沙，560公里，飞机1小时，高铁2小时20分钟
Dialogue: 2,0:02:17.16,0:02:24.18,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Trips like Guangzhou to Changsha, a distance of 350 miles, take an hour by plane or 2 hours and 20 minutes by train.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.36,0:02:27.82,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但算上飞机的值机、安检等等程序
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.36,0:02:27.82,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,When factoring in the time it takes to check in, go through security, and board
Dialogue: 1,0:02:27.88,0:02:31.78,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,坐火车在这两个城市旅行其实是很不错的选择
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.88,0:02:31.78,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,it absolutely makes sense to go by train when traveling between these two cities
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.78,0:02:35.26,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,更不用说（多数时候）高铁比机票便宜
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.78,0:02:35.26,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,even without considering that the high-speed train is cheaper than flying.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.52,0:02:40.04,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,对于更长的路线，高铁在中国也很不错，这在其他国家就行不通
Dialogue: 2,0:02:35.52,0:02:40.04,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,High speed rail even makes sense in China on longer routes where it wouldn’t in other countries.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:40.16,0:02:44.34,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,比如北京到上海，1050公里
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.16,0:02:44.34,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Beijing and Shanghai, for example, are about 650 miles apart.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:44.44,0:02:47.78,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,正常对于高铁来说距离就太远了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:44.44,0:02:47.78,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Normally that would be too far for high speed rail to make sense.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:47.88,0:02:52.92,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,巴黎到巴塞罗那，距离和北京到上海差不多
Dialogue: 2,0:02:47.88,0:02:52.92,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Paris and Barcelona, for example, are 500 miles apart—closer than Beijing and Shanghai
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.00,0:02:57.84,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,每天只有两次高铁，飞机却有20班
Dialogue: 2,0:02:53.00,0:02:57.84,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,—but only two high speed trains a day run between the two cities compared to about 20 flights.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:58.00,0:03:03.88,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而北京到上海，每天50班飞机、41次高铁
Dialogue: 2,0:02:58.00,0:03:03.88,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Between Beijing and Shanghai, on the other hand, about 50 flights run per day run compared to 41 trains.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:04.04,0:03:07.60,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,加之火车拉的人更多，可以达到1200人
Dialogue: 2,0:03:04.04,0:03:07.60,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Considering the trains carry far more people each, up to 1,200,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:07.70,0:03:11.58,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,因此火车才是承担两地客流的主要支柱
Dialogue: 2,0:03:07.70,0:03:11.58,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,trains are therefore the dominant means of transport between these two cities.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.76,0:03:14.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而京沪、巴黎巴塞罗那两条线路之间还有些区别
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.76,0:03:14.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,There are a few differences between these two routes.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.62,0:03:18.52,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,首先，京沪线耗时4小时28分
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.62,0:03:18.52,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,For one, while Beijing-Shanghai by train takes 4 hours and 28 minutes,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.60,0:03:23.50,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,巴黎到巴塞罗那，虽然距离更短，但却耗时6小时25分
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.60,0:03:23.50,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Paris-Barcelona, despite being a shorter distance, takes a longer 6 hours and 25 minutes.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:23.74,0:03:26.32,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,另外一个不同是航空业的竞争
Dialogue: 2,0:03:23.74,0:03:26.32,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The other factor, though, is about the competition.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:26.52,0:03:32.32,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,欧洲的民航网络非常发达，机票远远比火车票便宜
Dialogue: 2,0:03:26.52,0:03:32.32,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Europe has an efficient air transport network dominated by budget airlines that are often far cheaper than trains.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:32.38,0:03:36.70,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,巴黎到巴塞罗那机票也就12刀
Dialogue: 2,0:03:32.38,0:03:36.70,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,You can find tickets for flights between Paris and Barcelona for as little as $12
Dialogue: 1,0:03:36.82,0:03:40.34,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但最便宜的京沪线机票却要74刀
Dialogue: 2,0:03:36.82,0:03:40.34,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,while the cheapest Beijing-Shanghai flights go for $74.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.42,0:03:43.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国的民航真的太辣鸡
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.42,0:03:43.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Air travel within China is also far from efficient.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.64,0:03:47.82,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国三大航：南航、东航、国航
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.64,0:03:47.82,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,China Southern, China Eastern, and Air China, the three largest Chinese airlines,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:47.92,0:03:53.28,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,准点率分别是67%，66%，63%
Dialogue: 2,0:03:47.92,0:03:53.28,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,arrive on time an average of 67%, 66%, and 63% of the time respectively.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:53.40,0:03:57.48,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,其重要原因是空域太少
Dialogue: 2,0:03:53.40,0:03:57.48,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,A big reason for this is that there’s just not enough room in the skies.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:57.73,0:04:00.58,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国空域绝大多数都归军方管制
Dialogue: 2,0:03:57.73,0:04:00.58,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,A majority of China’s airspace is military controlled
Dialogue: 1,0:04:00.58,0:04:06.62,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,使得大约只有30%的狭窄空域是给民航使用的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:00.58,0:04:06.62,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,meaning that there are just these narrow flight corridors that account for 30% of airspace where civilian planes can fly.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:06.74,0:04:09.34,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,大量的飞机挤在如此狭小的空域
Dialogue: 2,0:04:06.74,0:04:09.34,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,With tons of planes and not much room to fly
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.34,0:04:13.36,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,导致大量飞机因为等待管制放行而延误
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.34,0:04:13.36,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,planes are frequently delayed by air traffic control to wait for the airspace to clear up 
Dialogue: 1,0:04:13.44,0:04:16.76,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,从而导致中国的航司准点率如此之惨
Dialogue: 2,0:04:13.44,0:04:16.76,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,which leads to the abysmal on-time ratings of the country’s airlines.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:16.84,0:04:19.76,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,所以虽说飞京沪线只要两小时
Dialogue: 2,0:04:16.84,0:04:19.76,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,While the Beijing-Shanghai flight takes only two hours,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:19.76,0:04:23.96,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但潜在的延误、加上其他各种因素，导致坐飞机真不快
Dialogue: 2,0:04:19.76,0:04:23.96,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,the potential of delays, along with all the other factors that make air travel slower,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:23.96,0:04:27.82,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,也使得高铁成为人们更青睐的交通工具
Dialogue: 2,0:04:23.96,0:04:27.82,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,help make the train the popular means of transport on this longer route.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:28.04,0:04:30.86,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但中国其他高铁线路就让人看不懂了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.04,0:04:30.86,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Other train routes in China, though, make less sense.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:30.96,0:04:36.20,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,比如在2014年新开通了一条兰州到乌鲁木齐的高铁线路
Dialogue: 2,0:04:30.96,0:04:36.20,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,For example, in 2014, the new high speed train line opened between Lanzhou and Urumqi.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:36.36,0:04:39.40,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这俩城市在中国都不算大城市
Dialogue: 2,0:04:36.36,0:04:39.40,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,These two cities are relatively small by China standards.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:39.54,0:04:44.36,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,都有350万人口，沿途全是小镇子
Dialogue: 2,0:04:39.54,0:04:44.36,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,They both have a population of 3.5 million and between them are only small towns.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.44,0:04:48.60,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,离得也特远，相距1600公里
Dialogue: 2,0:04:44.44,0:04:48.60,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,They’re also not close—about 1,000 miles separate them.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.72,0:04:52.98,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,相当于在美国建一条从丹佛到西雅图的高铁
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.72,0:04:52.98,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,This project could therefore be compared to building a high speed train from Denver to Seattle
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.12,0:04:57.20,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这俩也是中等城市，离得很远，中间也没有大城市
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.12,0:04:57.20,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,—they’re modestly sized cities a long way’s apart with nothing big in between.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.38,0:05:00.98,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,或许会有人坐，但绝对没法挣钱
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.38,0:05:00.98,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Some people would use it but it wouldn’t make any financial sense.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.19,0:05:06.20,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,在中国，兰州和鸟市不算小，但中间也真没大城市
Dialogue: 2,0:05:01.19,0:05:06.20,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,In China, Lanzhou and Urumqi are not small cities but there’s really nothing big in between
Dialogue: 1,0:05:06.20,0:05:09.40,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而且这个距离也实在想不出不坐飞机的理由
Dialogue: 2,0:05:06.20,0:05:09.40,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,and, at that distance, there’s no sense not flying.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:09.58,0:05:14.72,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,兰州到鸟市，高铁耗时11小时，飞机只要两个半小时
Dialogue: 2,0:05:09.58,0:05:14.72,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The Lanzhou-Urumqi high speed train takes 11 hours compared to the 2.5 hour flight
Dialogue: 1,0:05:14.86,0:05:18.22,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,高铁造价200亿刀
Dialogue: 2,0:05:14.86,0:05:18.22,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,and the construction cost of that line was $20 billion
Dialogue: 1,0:05:18.22,0:05:21.06,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,说明如果每列高铁都坐满
Dialogue: 2,0:05:18.22,0:05:21.06,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,meaning that if every seat on every train was filled
Dialogue: 1,0:05:21.06,0:05:27.22,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,单程票价需要达到400刀才能在30年内收回建造成本
Dialogue: 2,0:05:21.06,0:05:27.22,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,tickets would still have to cost $400 each way just to make back the construction cost in 30 years.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:27.36,0:05:31.42,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,实际票价只有80刀，且根本坐不满
Dialogue: 2,0:05:27.36,0:05:31.42,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,In reality tickets cost about $80 and trains are far from full
Dialogue: 1,0:05:31.42,0:05:35.50,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,说明这线路完全是在赔本运行
Dialogue: 2,0:05:31.42,0:05:35.50,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,meaning that this rail line is just insanely far from profitable.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:35.60,0:05:40.48,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,票价带来的收入连线路电费都不够
Dialogue: 2,0:05:35.60,0:05:40.48,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The ticket revenues from these trains reportedly don’t even cover the cost of electricity for the line
Dialogue: 1,0:05:40.48,0:05:43.22,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,更不要说建造成本和其它运营成本
Dialogue: 2,0:05:40.48,0:05:43.22,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,let alone construction and other operating costs.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:43.32,0:05:49.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,那为什么中国政府如此下血本造一条根本不可能挣钱的高铁线路呢？
Dialogue: 2,0:05:43.32,0:05:49.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,So why would the Chinese government sink so much money into something that has no prospects of really ever making money?
Dialogue: 1,0:05:49.76,0:05:51.22,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,答案是政治原因
Dialogue: 2,0:05:49.76,0:05:51.22,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Well, politics.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:51.32,0:05:54.12,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,鸟市是新疆维吾尔自治区的首府
Dialogue: 2,0:05:51.32,0:05:54.12,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Urumqi is the capital of the Xinjiang province.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:54.22,0:05:59.80,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,92%的中国人是汉族，而新疆有很多的维吾尔族
Dialogue: 2,0:05:54.22,0:05:59.80,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,While 92% of China’s population is Han Chinese, the Xinjiang province is primarily Uyghur
Dialogue: 1,0:05:59.92,0:06:01.84,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,维族是中国少数民族之一
Dialogue: 2,0:05:59.92,0:06:01.84,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,—one of the minority ethnic groups of China
Dialogue: 1,0:06:01.84,0:06:07.90,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,那边一直有很强的分裂势力，曾经常弄出暴力事件
Dialogue: 2,0:06:01.84,0:06:07.90,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,—and there has been an ongoing fairly strong separatist movement by the Uyghurs from China that has often turned violent.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:08.00,0:06:13.70,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,北京则想让新疆和国家其余部分那样同化
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.00,0:06:13.70,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The central government in Beijing, however, wants the Xinjiang province to be just as integrated as the rest of the country
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.80,0:06:16.02,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,并采取了很多强制措施
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.80,0:06:16.02,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,and has tried a variety of methods to force this
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.02,0:06:21.86,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,比如送很多汉人进入自治区、送一些维族进所谓的“再教育营”
Dialogue: 2,0:06:16.02,0:06:21.86,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,including moving Han Chinese into the region and the imprisonment of Uyghurs in so-called “reeducation camps.”
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.01,0:06:27.78,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,修高铁也是最新的、让新疆离首都更近的一种手段罢了，不是啥秘密
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.01,0:06:27.78,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The high-speed train is just the most recent tactic to bring Xinjiang closer to Beijing and this is no secret.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:27.86,0:06:33.72,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,政府一直在说修这条线路是为了促进民族团结
Dialogue: 2,0:06:27.86,0:06:33.72,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The central government is fully upfront in saying that the line was built to promote, as they call it, “ethnic unity.”
Dialogue: 1,0:06:33.79,0:06:37.60,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这也不是中国第一次用铁路作为政治手段了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:33.79,0:06:37.60,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,This isn’t even the first time they’ve used this tactic of railroad politics.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:37.68,0:06:41.52,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,西藏，和新疆一样也有一股分裂势力
Dialogue: 2,0:06:37.68,0:06:41.52,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Tibet, a region even better known than Xinjiang for its independence movement,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:41.60,0:06:46.68,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,是中国最后一个没有通铁路的省份，因为那里人口少、地形复杂
Dialogue: 2,0:06:41.60,0:06:46.68,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,was the last region in China not to have a railway due to its small population and intense terrain.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:46.82,0:06:52.48,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中央决定修一条铁路拉近西藏与首都的距离，于是青藏铁路诞生了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:46.82,0:06:52.48,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The central government still wanted to build one, though, to bring it closer to the rest of the country and so they did.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:52.70,0:06:59.50,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,如今火车可以在47小时内从北京到拉萨，开上全世界海拔最高的铁路
Dialogue: 2,0:06:52.70,0:06:59.50,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Trains now run directly from Beijing to Lhasa, Tibet in 47 hours on the highest elevation rail line in the world.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:59.70,0:07:07.10,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,海拔可达5071米，高到乘客需要氧气供应
Dialogue: 2,0:06:59.70,0:07:07.10,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,These trains reach an elevation of 16,640 feet—so high that passengers have to use a direct oxygen supply.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:07.24,0:07:11.98,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而北京到香港的高铁也是中央为了拉近香港的距离
Dialogue: 2,0:07:07.24,0:07:11.98,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Even the train to Hong Kong serves the central government’s goal of further integrating Hong Kong
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.02,0:07:15.64,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,香港和中国大陆不同，是一个特别行政区
Dialogue: 2,0:07:12.02,0:07:15.64,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,which is an autonomous special administrative region, into mainland China.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:15.75,0:07:20.62,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,虽说北京到香港的高铁比兰州鸟市高铁更能让人理解
Dialogue: 2,0:07:15.75,0:07:20.62,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,While high-speed trains to Hong Kong certainly do make a lot more sense than trains to the Xinjiang province
Dialogue: 1,0:07:20.62,0:07:23.36,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,很多香港人却也不欢迎它来
Dialogue: 2,0:07:20.62,0:07:23.36,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,many Hong Kongers have not greeted the new service kindly
Dialogue: 1,0:07:23.36,0:07:27.75,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,他们认为这是对香港基本法的侵犯
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.36,0:07:27.75,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,as they view it as an encroachment on the autonomy guaranteed to them by Hong Kong Basic Law.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:27.75,0:07:30.78,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,最有争议的其实不是火车
Dialogue: 2,0:07:27.75,0:07:30.78,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The most controversial part has not been the fact that there’s a train
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.78,0:07:35.26,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而是在香港的那站里现在有一部分归中国大陆了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.78,0:07:35.26,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,but rather that the station in Hong Kong includes an area that is effectively now part of Mainland China
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.26,0:07:38.94,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,人们在香港上火车之前要先过边检了
Dialogue: 2,0:07:35.26,0:07:38.94,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,since people pass through border controls before boarding the train in Hong Kong.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:39.18,0:07:43.74,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,和其他国家类似，中国修建高铁网络的目的
Dialogue: 2,0:07:39.18,0:07:43.74,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Just like any country, what having a high-speed, efficient rail network in China is doing
Dialogue: 1,0:07:43.74,0:07:46.20,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,就是把让国家更加统一更加强大
Dialogue: 2,0:07:43.74,0:07:46.20,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,is bringing the country together and making it stronger
Dialogue: 1,0:07:46.20,0:07:49.14,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,即使有些地方的人还想搞分裂
Dialogue: 2,0:07:46.20,0:07:49.14,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,even if it’s bringing together people that want to stay apart.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:49.24,0:07:50.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,不管目的如何
Dialogue: 2,0:07:49.24,0:07:50.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,No matter their motives, 
Dialogue: 1,0:07:50.54,0:07:55.62,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国建造高铁的效率是比其他任何国家都快的
Dialogue: 2,0:07:50.54,0:07:55.62,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,it’s clear that China is building their high speed rail network more efficiently than any other country.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:55.70,0:08:01.33,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,作为对比，这是加州旧金山到洛圣都的高铁规划
Dialogue: 2,0:07:55.70,0:08:01.33,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,To compare, this is the plan for California’s high speed rail line from San Francisco to the Los Angeles area.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:01.33,0:08:06.42,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,其目前还在建设的最初阶段，预计2029年通车
Dialogue: 2,0:08:01.33,0:08:06.42,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,It’s currently in very early phases of construction and is expected to open by 2029.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:06.72,0:08:11.24,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,说明加州建完这一条线路的时间
Dialogue: 2,0:08:06.72,0:08:11.24,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Of course that means that the time it will take for the California’s high speed rail network to go from this to this
Dialogue: 1,0:08:11.24,0:08:15.16,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,和中国建完全国高铁网络的时间差不多
Dialogue: 2,0:08:11.24,0:08:15.16,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,is the same as the time it took China’s high speed rail network to go from this to this
Dialogue: 1,0:08:15.16,0:08:17.48,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,同时注意下造价
Dialogue: 2,0:08:15.16,0:08:17.48,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,But, the main thing to look at is cost.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:17.60,0:08:23.00,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,加州高铁预计造价770亿刀，520英里长
Dialogue: 2,0:08:17.60,0:08:23.00,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,This Californian network is expected to cost $77 billion and is 520 miles long
Dialogue: 1,0:08:23.00,0:08:26.96,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,平均每英里1.48亿刀
Dialogue: 2,0:08:23.00,0:08:26.96,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,meaning that it will cost $148 million per mile to build.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:27.12,0:08:32.22,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而中国的高铁网络，平均每英里造价只有3000万刀
Dialogue: 2,0:08:27.12,0:08:32.22,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,China, on the other hand, is building their network at a cost of only $30 million per mile.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:32.32,0:08:38.02,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,当然中国的劳动力比较便宜，且铁路所经之处比较偏远，地价不高
Dialogue: 2,0:08:32.32,0:08:38.02,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Of course labor costs are lower in China and their network crosses more rural areas where land acquisition costs are lower
Dialogue: 1,0:08:38.02,0:08:43.18,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但中国最牛逼的是他们把高铁建设几乎变成了一条生产线
Dialogue: 2,0:08:38.02,0:08:43.18,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,But, what’s more meaningful is that they’ve turned building high speed rail into almost an assembly line process
Dialogue: 1,0:08:43.28,0:08:47.48,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,从而让高架桥、隧道等很多造价高昂的基建量产化
Dialogue: 2,0:08:43.28,0:08:47.48,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,where they can mass produce even the most expensive elements like viaducts and tunnels.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:47.64,0:08:51.88,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国正在让高铁变得廉价化
Dialogue: 2,0:08:47.64,0:08:51.88,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,In true Chinese fashion, with scale they’re making high-speed cheaper.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:52.18,0:08:54.96,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国与其他西方国家最大的不同
Dialogue: 2,0:08:52.18,0:08:54.96,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The big difference between China and a lot of the western world,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:54.96,0:08:59.02,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,——尤其是像美国、加拿大、澳大利亚、新西兰、英国
Dialogue: 2,0:08:54.96,0:08:59.02,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,particularly countries like the US, Canada, Australia, New Zealand, and the UK,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:59.02,0:09:02.28,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,——是中国政府把高铁建设摆在首位
Dialogue: 2,0:08:59.02,0:09:02.28,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,is that high speed rail is at the top of the government’s priorities.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:02.28,0:09:07.17,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,在很多方面，中国政府都会把社会利益
Dialogue: 2,0:09:02.28,0:09:07.17,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Unsurprisingly given their government structure, in many ways, China has placed social benefit,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:07.17,0:09:09.30,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,——至少是他们定义的“社会价值”
Dialogue: 2,0:09:07.17,0:09:09.30,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,at least by the definition of the central government,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:09.36,0:09:12.50,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,——放在单纯的线路利润之前
Dialogue: 2,0:09:09.36,0:09:12.50,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,ahead of profitability when developing their high speed rail network.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:12.68,0:09:17.30,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,高铁线路可能利润不如飞机等其他交通工具多
Dialogue: 2,0:09:12.68,0:09:17.30,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,High-speed rail lines just aren’t as profitable as other means of transport like planes
Dialogue: 1,0:09:17.30,0:09:19.60,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但它毫无疑问对国家是有利的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:17.30,0:09:19.60,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,but they are undoubtably better for countries
Dialogue: 1,0:09:19.60,0:09:23.86,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,所以当你考虑其总体利润的时候，一定要算上其带来的社会利益
Dialogue: 2,0:09:19.60,0:09:23.86,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,so you have to consider the social benefit when looking at their overall profitability.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:24.14,0:09:27.16,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,比如之前说的加州高铁线路
Dialogue: 2,0:09:24.14,0:09:27.16,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,For the San Francisco to LA high speed rail route, for example,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:27.16,0:09:32.34,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,一项研究发现，这条线路所降低的碳排放、所提高的生产力
Dialogue: 2,0:09:27.16,0:09:32.34,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,one study found that the social benefit derived from lower carbon emissions, higher worker productivity,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:32.34,0:09:38.10,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,和所减少的公路致命事故的损失可达每年4.4亿刀
Dialogue: 2,0:09:32.34,0:09:38.10,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,and reduced casualties from fewer people on the road would be equivalent to about $440 million per year.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:38.24,0:09:43.94,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,结果，这和政府扶持线路建设的钱基本扯平了
Dialogue: 2,0:09:38.24,0:09:43.94,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,As it turns out, this is almost the exact amount that the state will have to subsidize the line for it to break even.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:44.10,0:09:48.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国铁路总公司作为一个国有企业，挣的钱不但不多
Dialogue: 2,0:09:44.10,0:09:48.54,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The China Railway Corporation, a state owned enterprise, is actually slightly profitable,
Dialogue: 1,0:09:48.62,0:09:52.06,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,还有很多外债，还要靠国家的扶持
Dialogue: 2,0:09:48.62,0:09:52.06,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,although it does have huge amounts of debts and is helped by government subsidies.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:52.26,0:09:55.16,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但高铁对全中国人民带来的利益，是非常巨大的
Dialogue: 2,0:09:52.26,0:09:55.16,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The benefit to the Chinese people, though, is huge.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:55.28,0:10:01.06,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,高铁让在花销高昂的北上广打拼的人们
Dialogue: 2,0:09:55.28,0:10:01.06,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The high-speed rail allows those who can’t afford to live in the most expensive cities like Beijing, Shanghai, and Guangzhou
Dialogue: 1,0:10:01.06,0:10:04.00,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,能够轻松乘高铁去其他城市
Dialogue: 2,0:10:01.06,0:10:04.00,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,to easily commute from cheaper suburbs by high-speed rail.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:04.20,0:10:10.31,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,也多亏了高铁，7500万人可以在一小时内坐高铁去上海
Dialogue: 2,0:10:04.20,0:10:10.31,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Thanks to the high-speed rail, there are now 75 million people who can commute to Shanghai in under an hour.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:10.50,0:10:16.34,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,原本就很大的城市更是如虎添翼，而对于城市来说，规模就是力量
Dialogue: 2,0:10:10.50,0:10:16.34,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,It is growing what are already some of the largest cities and, when it comes to cities, size is strength.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:16.58,0:10:21.62,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,这些东部城市的高铁线路是全世界最赚钱的铁路线路
Dialogue: 2,0:10:16.58,0:10:21.62,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,These lines connecting the east’s largest cities are some of the most profitable rail lines in the world
Dialogue: 1,0:10:21.66,0:10:24.24,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,也让在中国居住、工作的人们生活更加便利
Dialogue: 2,0:10:21.66,0:10:24.24,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,and they’re making living and working in China easier.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:24.24,0:10:30.02,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,下一个问题是，回顾过去几十年，高铁途径小城市将来是否有意义？
Dialogue: 2,0:10:24.24,0:10:30.02,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,But the question is, when we look back decades from now, whether the high-speed trains to smaller cities will have made sense?
Dialogue: 1,0:10:30.23,0:10:33.42,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,因为要在大城市间尽量走直线
Dialogue: 2,0:10:30.23,0:10:33.42,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Out of a desire to keep the lines going straight between the big cities,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:33.50,0:10:38.22,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,高铁途径的几个小城市的车站通常离市中心很远的郊区
Dialogue: 2,0:10:33.50,0:10:38.22,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,the stops for smaller cities are often out in the countryside dozens of miles away from the city core.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:38.42,0:10:42.30,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,衡阳——一百万人口的小城市——的高铁站
Dialogue: 2,0:10:38.42,0:10:42.30,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The high speed station for Hengyang, for example, a smaller city of only a million,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:42.30,0:10:45.52,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,在市中心45分钟车程的西边
Dialogue: 2,0:10:42.30,0:10:45.52,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,is about a 45 minute drive east of the city center.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:45.70,0:10:48.68,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,虽然城市希望未来以车站为中心发展
Dialogue: 2,0:10:45.70,0:10:48.68,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,The hope is that new development will spring up around the stations
Dialogue: 1,0:10:48.76,0:10:51.86,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,但这样的网络结构，即使在火车上省了时间
Dialogue: 2,0:10:48.76,0:10:51.86,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,but this network structure, even if it saves time on the train,
Dialogue: 1,0:10:51.86,0:10:55.84,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,却在前后去车站的路上浪费了，这又降低了高铁的效益
Dialogue: 2,0:10:51.86,0:10:55.84,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,wastes time before and after which degrades the benefit of high-speed rail.
Dialogue: 1,0:10:56.02,0:10:59.32,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,总之，中国是世界上第一个
Dialogue: 2,0:10:56.02,0:10:59.32,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,In all, China is really the first country to have experimented
Dialogue: 1,0:10:59.32,0:11:02.92,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,长距离穿越其西部人口稀少地区的国家
Dialogue: 2,0:10:59.32,0:11:02.92,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,with long-distance, high speed rail through less-dense areas in its west.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:03.04,0:11:06.94,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而在东部，高铁则推动了全国的经济发展
Dialogue: 2,0:11:03.04,0:11:06.94,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,In the east, though, these trains are enlarging the country’s economic power.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:07.02,0:11:11.78,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,而这也只是中国追赶其他发达国家的方法之一
Dialogue: 2,0:11:07.02,0:11:11.78,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,It’s just one of the many factors speeding up China’s catch-up with world’s richest countries.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:11.94,0:11:16.74,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,尽管中国正在以较小的速度建造列车，并在高铁建设方面进行创新
Dialogue: 2,0:11:11.94,0:11:16.74,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,Even though China is building these trains for less and innovating on the construction of high-speed rail
Dialogue: 1,0:11:16.74,0:11:20.36,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,中国如此擅长建造高铁的真正原因
Dialogue: 2,0:11:16.74,0:11:20.36,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,the real reason why China is so good at building railways is because
Dialogue: 1,0:11:20.36,0:11:26.46,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,是他们有建造高铁的政治需求——这是其他国家没有的
Dialogue: 2,0:11:20.36,0:11:26.46,1080EN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,they have the one thing that almost every other country lacks—the political will for high-speed trains.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:27.12,0:12:09.54,1080CN_BELOW,,0,0,0,,依然是防不胜防时间 链接在下面
